name: Cube 2 Demo File
summary: A DMO file is a game demo file created by various games using the Cube 2 game engine, such as Red Eclipse, Blood Frontier, and Cube 2: Sauerbraten. It contains a recording of a single or multiplayer session, including player movements, game events, and a chat log, in the Cube 2 Demo (DMO) format. DMO files enable games running the Cube 2 engine to replicate an exact replay of the match.
